claim.claim-text:
9. A process for the preparation of a pharmaceutical composition according to any one of claims 1 to 5, characterised in that: 
a) the active principle, the disintegrating agent and the sodium alkylsulfate are mixed at room temperature with a diluent, a binder and, optionally, a coloring agent; 
b) the mixture is wetted with purified water; 
c) the resulting wet mass is dried and graded; and 
d) a lubricant and, optionally, an antiadhesive, a flowing agent, a coloring agent and/or a flavoring agent are added to the resulting graded dry grains.
